MrLincoln, on the first reading of the resolutions, had inclined to vote in favor of concurring;
               but upon the second, he falt[felt] that he wanted more time for deliberation.  He now thought it would be better to
               postpone the subject indefinitely; and accordingly, made a motion to this effect.
